# fetchtype — Typography Validation

This project uses fetchtype for typography token validation and export.

## Key files

- `fetchtype.tokens.json` — typography, color, spacing, hierarchy tokens
- `.fetchtype.json` — rule configuration (optional)

## Workflow

```bash
# Validate tokens (run after any token change)
fetchtype validate -i fetchtype.tokens.json

# Export to framework
fetchtype build -i fetchtype.tokens.json --format tailwind
fetchtype build -i fetchtype.tokens.json --format shadcn
fetchtype build -i fetchtype.tokens.json --format all
```

## Token schema

The token file has sections: `typography` (12 contexts), `color` (light/dark), `hierarchy` (type scale, headings h1-h6), `spacing` (scale), `layout` (prose width, breakpoints).

Typography contexts: heading, subheading, body, caption, button, label, input, code, blockquote, chart-label, chart-axis, chart-title.

## Validation (20 rules)

Checks: WCAG AA contrast (4.5:1), body line-height >= 1.5, min font sizes, prose width <= 75ch, heading hierarchy, spacing monotonicity, dark mode completeness, font fallbacks, payload budgets, variable font axes, font-display strategy.

Run `fetchtype validate -i fetchtype.tokens.json` after modifying any token values.

## Font tools

```bash
fetchtype suggest -c interface    # Font recommendations by context
fetchtype pair "Inter"            # Pairing suggestions
fetchtype search "geometric sans" --variable  # Search 1,929 fonts
fetchtype resolve Inter           # Full font metadata
```

## MCP server

Add to `.cursor/mcp.json` for direct tool access:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "fetchtype": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["fetchtype", "mcp"]
    }
  }
}
```

## Export formats

CSS (`--format css`), Tailwind (`--format tailwind`), shadcn (`--format shadcn`), W3C Design Tokens (`--format w3c`), JSON (`--format json`), all (`--format all`).
